    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-01-11T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-01-11T16:00:00-05:00" n="430"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d430">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2531/241: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Frost</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-11T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 11, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Your 80, November 22, 7 p.m.,<note n="7" xml:id="d430fn7">
                        <ref target="frus1937v05#pg_417">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1937, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p. 417</ref>.</note> and 9, January 6, 1
                        p.m.<note n="8" xml:id="d430fn8">Not printed.</note> Please report whether
                        <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> signed January 6, 1938 went into force
                    either provisionally or definitively in Chile on day of signature. If it is not
                    now in force, when will it become effective?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
